Description: Machine Learning for Ecological Species Distribution Modeling (mlexsdm) is an R package that provides tools for developing, evaluating, and applying species distribution models using machine learning techniques. The package includes optimized functions for bioclimatic variable calculations using RcppParallel for high-performance computing.
